{"article_id":"kdBDnE26Di2dfq5J","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Devin Nunes speaks to reporters on Capitol Hill , October 2017 .","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"( Carlos Barria/Reuters )","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"The FBI and Democrats don ' t have good reasons","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"for wanting to prevent its disclosure to the public .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"It appears very likely that President Trump is going to allow the disclosure , in some form , of the memo on alleged FISA abuse","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"authored by majority staff of the House Intelligence Committee under the direction of Chairman Devin Nunes","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"( R. , Calif. ) .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"It could happen as early as today .","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"As one would expect ,","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"both sides of the dispute over the memo are intensifying their pre-publication efforts","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"to influence public reaction","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"- as discussed here in last week ' s column","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"considering objections to the memo .","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"Since before the Republican-led committee voted","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"( along partisan lines )","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"to seek the memo ' s declassification and publication ,","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"the FBI has been complaining","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"that it was not permitted to review the memo .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"As I explained last week ,","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"this was a very unpersuasive complaint .","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"Having stonewalled the committee ' s information requests for several months ,","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"the Bureau and Justice Department are hardly well positioned","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"to complain","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"about being denied access ;","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"the committee , by contrast , has every reason","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"to believe","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"they would have slow-walked any review","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"in order to delay matters further .","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"All that aside , the FBI was guaranteed access to the memo before its publication","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"because of the rules of the process .","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"Once the committee voted to disclose ,","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"that gave the president five days to object .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"During that five days , Trump ' s own appointees at the FBI and DOJ would have the chance","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"to pore over the memo","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"and make their objections and policy arguments to their principal , the president , and to the rest of the Trump national-security team .","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"This tells us","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"the real objection was not that they were barred from reviewing the memo ;","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"it is that they were barred from reviewing it on a schedule","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"that would make it more difficult to derail publication .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"Fox News reports","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"that FBI director Christopher Wray reviewed the memo on Capitol Hill on Sunday","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"-","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"before the committee even voted to release it .","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"Subsequently , two senior FBI officials","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"- one each from the Bureau ' s counterintelligence and legal divisions -","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"reviewed the memo","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"and \" could not point to any factual inaccuracies \" in it ,","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"according to an unnamed source","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"who spoke to Fox .","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"There has followed the usual gamesmanship","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"that intensifies public cynicism about \" the Swamp. \"","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"Based on their review of the memo ,","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"the FBI and committee Democrats sought some changes .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"Though committee Republicans did not agree","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"that these edits were necessary ,","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"they nevertheless agreed to make them .","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"Democrats promptly used this accommodation","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"- which they and the FBI had requested -","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"to argue","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"that publication should now be withheld","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"because the memo has been \" materially \" and \" substantively \" altered since the committee votes .","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"Nunes counters","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"that the edits are minor","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"and include mere grammatical fixes .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"Given that the people","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"who are complaining about the changes","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"are the ones","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"who insisted on them ,","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"the chairman rejects what he calls an \" increasingly strange attempt","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"to thwart publication of the memo . \"","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"Apparently unable to cite inaccuracies ,","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"the Bureau has shifted to the objection","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"we anticipated last week","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"- namely , that the memo takes things out of context .","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"The purported omission of material information ,","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"it is said ,","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"has the effect","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"of making the memo misleading .","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"The FBI put out a statement Wednesday","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"asserting","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"that it had \" grave concerns about material omissions of fact","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"that fundamentally impact the memo ' s accuracy . \"","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"The committee and such other informed critics as Senator Lindsey Graham have been suggesting","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"that the FBI and Justice Department used allegations from the Steele dossier in an application for a FISA Court warrant","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"but did not tell the judge important facts about the dossier","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"( specifically , that the dossier was an unverified anti-Trump opposition-research project ,","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"commissioned by the Hillary Clinton campaign ) .","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"Thus , Chairman Nunes ' s hard-edged response to the FBI ' s statement was what one would expect :","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"If anyone knows about \" material omissions , \"","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"it is the FBI .","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"\" It ' s clear , \"","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"Nunes states , \"","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"that top officials used unverified information in a court document","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"to fuel a counter-intelligence investigation during an American political campaign . \"","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"If the memo does not contain factual misstatements","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"and the major complaint is that it is incomplete","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"because salient facts are omitted ,","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"that is an easy problem to solve .","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"I elaborated on that in last week ' s column :","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"As with any summary , there is always a danger of [ the memo ' s ] being misleading .","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"This [ is comparable to ] a recurring problem in judicial proceedings ,","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"where the need","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"to boil voluminous information down to its essence","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"is obvious .","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"The problem is solved by the so-called rule of completeness :","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"If a party contends","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"that his adversary is taking information out of context","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"or otherwise omitting essential details necessary to an accurate understanding of a document ,","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"the party may propose","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"that the necessary context or details be included .","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"An example :","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"Smith tells the police ,","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"\" I was in the bank","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"but I didn ' t rob it. \"","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"At the trial , the prosecutor disingenuously suggests to the jury","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"that Smith was implicitly admitting guilt","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"when he told the police","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"\" I was in the bank \" the day","depth":15},{"id":118,"text":"it was robbed .","depth":15},{"id":119,"text":"Smith would then be entitled to introduce his complete statement","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"- the \" but I didn ' t rob it \" portion is necessary to the jury ' s understanding","depth":13},{"id":121,"text":"that ,","depth":14},{"id":122,"text":"far from implicitly admitting guilt ,","depth":15},{"id":123,"text":"Smith explicitly denied guilt .","depth":15},{"id":124,"text":"In the column , I was addressing claims by committee Democrats ,","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"but these echo the complaint","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"the FBI is making now .","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"We pointed out","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"that the simple way forward was for Democrats to propose the inclusion of any details necessary","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"to correct any misimpressions ,","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"or to prepare their own memo","depth":12},{"id":131,"text":"that would reveal the hidden details","depth":13},{"id":132,"text":"and illustrate","depth":14},{"id":133,"text":"that Republicans were engaged in partisan spin .","depth":14},{"id":134,"text":"In fact , committee Democrats have prepared a memo ,","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"which is under review","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"and should ultimately be released .","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"Obviously , the same option is available to the FBI .","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"In fact , it is more available to the FBI :","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"Unlike Congress , the bureau \" owns \" the classified information in the underlying documents .","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"The Bureau is thus well positioned to publish a declassified summary","depth":14},{"id":141,"text":"that discloses any details","depth":15},{"id":142,"text":"it says","depth":16},{"id":143,"text":"Nunes has mendaciously hidden ;","depth":16},{"id":144,"text":"or better yet , it could disclose the underlying documents","depth":14},{"id":145,"text":"( with any necessary redactions of classified information ) .","depth":14},{"id":146,"text":"I contended last week","depth":12},{"id":147,"text":"that Nunes , a smart guy , had to be well aware","depth":14},{"id":148,"text":"that this could be done","depth":14},{"id":149,"text":"and that he would look very foolish","depth":14},{"id":150,"text":"if ,","depth":15},{"id":151,"text":"when more facts were inevitably exposed ,","depth":16},{"id":152,"text":"it turned out he had put out a dishonest version of events .","depth":16},{"id":153,"text":"That ' s why I ' m encouraged by this part of his response to the FBI ' s statement :","depth":13},{"id":154,"text":"\" They","depth":15},{"id":155,"text":"[ i.e. , the Bureau ]","depth":15},{"id":156,"text":"are welcome to make public , to the greatest extent possible , all the information","depth":15},{"id":157,"text":"they have on the abuses . \"","depth":15},{"id":158,"text":"The point here is to preserve and protect the FBI as an institution ,","depth":13},{"id":159,"text":"which requires getting to the bottom of any potential effort","depth":14},{"id":160,"text":"to exploit the FBI for purposes of electoral politics .","depth":14},{"id":161,"text":"All along , the committee has been pushing for disclosure .","depth":13},{"id":162,"text":"The summary memo was written","depth":14},{"id":163,"text":"because the FBI and Justice Department objected to disclosure of the underlying classified information .","depth":14},{"id":164,"text":"Now , the FBI ' s objection is that the memo is not as complete as the underlying information .","depth":12},{"id":165,"text":"Either way , the point is to avoid public scrutiny .","depth":11},{"id":166,"text":"Two final thoughts .","depth":4},{"id":167,"text":"First , the coverage has tried to make this all about Nunes ,","depth":9},{"id":168,"text":"and then to lampoon him as alternatively cagy and clueless .","depth":9},{"id":169,"text":"In point of fact , Republicans on the committee and throughout the House have been solidly behind disclosure of the memo .","depth":9},{"id":170,"text":"Many of these are among law enforcement ' s strongest supporters .","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"These include Representative Trey Gowdy","depth":13},{"id":172,"text":"( R. , S.C. ) ,","depth":13},{"id":173,"text":"a respected former prosecutor","depth":13},{"id":174,"text":"who is part of the GOP mainstream ,","depth":13},{"id":175,"text":"and Representative Pete King","depth":13},{"id":176,"text":"( R. , N.Y. ) ,","depth":13},{"id":177,"text":"a moderate Republican","depth":13},{"id":178,"text":"who has been deeply involved in national-security issues .","depth":13},{"id":179,"text":"The point here is to preserve and protect the FBI as an institution ,","depth":8},{"id":180,"text":"which requires getting to the bottom of any potential effort","depth":9},{"id":181,"text":"to exploit the FBI for purposes of electoral politics .","depth":9},{"id":182,"text":"Democrats used to think","depth":7},{"id":183,"text":"diligent oversight of the FBI ' s exercise of national-security powers was pretty important .","depth":7},{"id":184,"text":"Second , usually we only find out about claimed abuses of national-security power","depth":8},{"id":185,"text":"when they are illegally leaked to the press ,","depth":9},{"id":186,"text":"which then risks compromising vital intelligence operations","depth":10},{"id":187,"text":"by publishing classified information .","depth":10},{"id":188,"text":"Generally , the media and Democrats fiercely defend this practice .","depth":7},{"id":189,"text":"Here , Nunes and the intelligence committee have gone about things the right way :","depth":9},{"id":190,"text":"not leaking ,","depth":11},{"id":191,"text":"conducting oversight ,","depth":12},{"id":192,"text":"and carefully handling classified information","depth":12},{"id":193,"text":"so that the things","depth":13},{"id":194,"text":"the public should know","depth":13},{"id":195,"text":"are disclosed","depth":12},{"id":196,"text":"without compromising vital intelligence and its sources .","depth":11},{"id":197,"text":"Yet , Democrats are condemning the process","depth":9},{"id":198,"text":"and much of the media seems strangely indifferent ,","depth":11},{"id":199,"text":"if not opposed ,","depth":11},{"id":200,"text":"to disclosure .","depth":10},{"id":201,"text":"It ' s almost as if the press can not get behind public accountability","depth":8},{"id":202,"text":"unless it is the New York Times , rather than a congressional committee ,","depth":9},{"id":203,"text":"deciding what gets published","depth":10},{"id":204,"text":"and which government operations warrant careful examination .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":409,"left":206,"right":408,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":206,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":408,"left":242,"right":407,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":242,"left":211,"right":241,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":211,"left":207,"right":210,"relation":"evalu